  "text": "Older adults with recent hip fractures are an important clinical group at increased risk of muscular disuse, declines in mobility and progressive disability [CITATION_1] . This population of older adults often presents to hospitals with multiple co-morbidities and impairments which may impede functional recovery [CITATION_2] .",
